Obviously not. The monster just roared and tried to charge directly at Sasalin. Thank goodness, although Sasalin was huge, he was still quite agile and managed to dodge in time. However, Nishi couldn't help but scream and almost slid off Sasalin's smooth scales.
"How can we kill them?" Nishi shouted.
"Aim for their heads!"
"This is too hard!"
Sasalin roared, circled around, and flew toward the mountain he called home. The black monster followed closely, but when it was attacked from behind by fire, it became somewhat panicked. The monster had yet to realize it had gained another opponent. Sasalin slowed down and then struck the monster's head with his tail, knocking it off course. The monster became even more panicked.
The monster roared, hissing from his throat as he flew straight upward, continuously spitting something into the air. Suddenly, everything around them turned pitch black, as if the monster was absorbing the light from the sky and replacing it with an eternal darkness.
Sasalin's vision went dark, and he tried to retreat, but he found himself colliding with tree branches and then falling onto the ground. The monster apparently knew exactly where Sasalin had fallen and flew directly toward him, bringing the cloud of darkness with it.
"Kayer!" Trenuk shouted, flying out of the cloud and beginning to circle, trying to find Nishi and Sasalin in the darkness below. "What should we do, Kayer...? Kayer, where are you?"
Nishi struggled to her feet. She felt sure she had broken some bones, but her strange, unnatural healing ability had already begun to take effect. Sasalin's situation was different; he lay helplessly on the ground, leaning against a tree he had crushed. Nishi tried to walk toward Sasalin, but her vision was completely dark, and she could barely see anything. Terrifying shadows surrounded her, and something was screeching within the shadows.
A terrible club-like tail smashed down onto the ground, knocking Nishi off her feet. She noticed the tail was swinging wildly, but it seemed its target was not her. Nishi barely saw the monster roaring and frantically scratching at the shadows it had created. Something was teleporting within the darkness, waiting for the perfect moment to strike the monster.
Suddenly, a gunshot shattered the air, and the monster instantly fell silent, collapsing motionless on the ground. The surrounding darkness dissipated, revealing the truth of the situation. Kayer stood on top of the monster's corpse, holding a rifle, panting heavily.
"That was... one of the weirdest shadow jumps I've ever done... Tanto Katoron..." Kayer gasped, catching his breath. For some reason, his eyes glowed with black light, and a dark energy surged within him. However, as Kayer spoke, his organic armor regained its color, and his eyes returned to their normal yellow.
After a while, Nishi finally understood what had happened. They all knew that Kayer possessed strange shadow abilities, but he rarely used them because most people believed such abilities were extremely evil and terrifying. However, Nishi didn't know that Kayer could use this ability in any darkness. Moreover, from Kayer's expression, it seemed that even he was quite surprised himself.
"Are you okay?" Nishi couldn't help but ask.
"I'm fine. I killed that thing, and I'll be back to normal soon." Kayer looked at his "masterpiece," and at that moment, Trenuk landed beside him, transforming back into his original Spast form.
Now that the monster was no longer moving, they could take a good look at what it actually was. Its skin was pitch black and glossy, covered in a layer of sticky liquid that clung tightly to the monster's body. It had four wings and four legs, with each leg ending in long, slender claws, and two straight horns growing from its skull.
Before Trenuk and Kayer could even ask what kind of creature this was, another monster screeched and leaped out from the nearby bushes. At that moment, a familiar car crashed into the side of the monster, causing it to slide a short distance before coming to a stop at Nishi's feet. Without hesitation, Nishi grabbed her shotgun and fired a shot directly at the monster's head, killing it instantly.
"Ouch..." Retwick muttered from the driver's seat, then awkwardly turned off the engine and climbed down from the truck. "Uh, I didn't mean to. Are you all okay?"
"You missed all the fun!" Trenuk grumbled. "Where did you go?"
"You left me behind. I did my best to catch up..." Retwick sighed. "Excuse me, what were those terrible things?"
Retwick's question was answered by Sasalin, who had already gotten up. He was covered in wounds and scratches, looking a bit dazed, but his injuries didn't seem too serious.
"You killed the Corrupted! Those infected monsters. When the Corrupted attacked your god, these creatures were left behind here."
"You mean... we... helped kill the terrible monster god?" Trenuk stuttered slightly.
"Yes, that's right. There may be more Corrupted. But I can't shoot them in the head. I don't have a gun. And it's not fair to fight two against one, right?" Sasalin walked up to Kayer and patted his head. "Thank you, little one. You reminded me of my old friend Arcading. Just you aren't as ruthless as him, nor do you have his ability to destroy the universe."
"Uh... thank you... I guess..." Kayer shrugged. "So, uh, did we finish the mission?"
Nishi shrugged, picked up her camera, and took a few photos of the monsters that were definitely dead. Then, she pulled out her favorite dagger—the beautiful Reaper Dagger—and began cutting off one of the monster's horns, then the other. However, the moment Nishi finished cutting, the monsters suddenly began to self-combust, quickly turning into a pile of ashes. The horns Nishi had cut off also turned to ashes.
"Well... that's certainly a mixed blessing..." Nishi sighed. "At least I still have the photos, right?"
